The paper focuses on improving face detection performance using synthetic data generated from a 3D face dataset. This falls under computer vision (cs.CV) as the primary sub-category. The use of 3D rendering also suggests a possible fit with graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The investigation of the influence of different variations on face detection performance suggests a possible fit with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
